pred_item.name: Bifidobacterium animalis ssp. lactis Bl-04
pred_item.description: The daily dose of probiotic was provided in a sachet containing a minimum of 2 x 10^9 colony forming units of Bl-04 mixed with 1g of sucrose as a carrier.

pred_item.name: Placebo
pred_item.description: The placebo was provided as a sachet containing 1g of sucrose that was identical to the study product in appearance, smell, and taste.

ref_item.measure: Number of Participants With Rhinovirus-associated Illness Episodes
ref_item.description: Rhinovirus-associated illness episodes: Volunteers who have both a rhinovirus infection and a symptomatic illness will be defined as having a rhinovirus-associated common cold illness.

pred_item.description: Illness that met the study criteria for illness in a volunteer who also met the definition for RV infection. Symptomatic illness defined as total symptom score of at least 6 and either three days of rhinorrhea or the subjective impression of a common cold illness.
